# Digital IC Design Internship

## Overview

This repository documents the work completed during my **Digital IC Design Internship**. It contains the Verilog designs, documentation, presentations, reports, and learning outcomes from each day of the internship.

The internship provided hands-on exposure to digital hardware design, RTL development, simulation, synthesis, and ASIC design methodologies using industry-standard Cadence EDA tools.

> **Note:** Cadence project files are not included in this repository due to confidentiality restrictions. Only the Verilog source code, reports, presentations, and other non-confidential materials are shared.

---

## Technologies Used

- Verilog HDL
- Cadence Xcelium (Simulation)
- Cadence Genus (Synthesis)
- Linux Environment
- Git & GitHub

---

## Skills Gained

During the internship, I gained practical experience in:

- RTL design using Verilog HDL
- Designing combinational and sequential digital circuits
- Functional simulation and debugging
- Logic synthesis and report analysis
- Understanding the ASIC digital design flow
- Technical documentation and version control

